                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                             An Apache POI fuzzing harness was run successfully, producing extensive instrumentation logs but no build errors. A follow-up patch attempt added four field                        
                             declarations (`sInf`, `dsInf`, `directory`, and a second `LOG`) to `POIDocument.java`. When rebuilding, the compiler reported duplicatevariable errors for each of                 
                             those fields, causing the `:poi:compileJava` task to fail.                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Initial issue                                                                                                                                                                       
                              A Jazzer-based fuzzer (`POIHSSFFuzzer`) was invoked against Apache POI. The fuzzer setup and run commands completed without compile errors, and the logs show                     
                             hundreds of classes being instrumented successfully.                                                                                                                                
                              There was no failure in the initial harness build or compile phase; the logs end with successful fuzzer invocation under libFuzzer.                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Patch attempt                                                                                                                                                                       
                             The following hunk was applied to `poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/POIDocument.java` beginning at line 63:                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             --- a/poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/POIDocument.java                                                                                                                             
                             +++ b/poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/POIDocument.java                                                                                                                             
                             @@ -63,6 +63,14 @@                                                                                                                                                                  
                                  private static final Logger LOG = PoiLogManager.getLogger(POIDocument.class);                                                                                                  
                             +    private SummaryInformation sInf;                                                                                                                                               
                             +    /** Holds further metadata on our document */                                                                                                                                  
                             +    private DocumentSummaryInformation dsInf;                                                                                                                                      
                             +    /** The directory that our document lives in */                                                                                                                                
                             +    private DirectoryNode directory;                                                                                                                                               
                             +                                                                                                                                                                                   
                             +    /** For our own logging use */                                                                                                                                                 
                             +    private static final Logger LOG = PoiLogManager.getLogger(POIDocument.class);                                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Result of patch                                                                                                                                                                     
                              The compiler produced errors in `POIDocument.java` on the new lines:                                                                                                              
                                variable sInf is already defined in class org.apache.poi.POIDocument                                                                                                          
                                variable dsInf is already defined in class org.apache.poi.POIDocument                                                                                                         
                                variable directory is already defined in class org.apache.poi.POIDocument                                                                                                     
                                variable LOG is already defined in class org.apache.poi.POIDocument                                                                                                           
                              These duplicatedefinition errors prevented the `:poi:compileJava` task from succeeding and caused the overall build to fail.                                                     
                              Several unrelated deprecation and uncheckedcast warnings were also emitted across other classes but did not themselves block the build.                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Areas for further investigation                                                                                                                                                     
                              Examine the existing field declarations in `POIDocument.java` to reconcile why `sInf`, `dsInf`, `directory`, and `LOG` were already defined.                                      
                              Audit the class to ensure there are no accidental duplicate sections or merge artifacts.                                                                                          
                              Verify whether additional logging or metadata fields are meant to be added, relocated, or renamed rather than redundantly declared.

                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Root-Cause Analysis                                                                                                                                                              
                                - The compilation failures stem from redeclaring fields (`sInf`, `dsInf`, `directory`) and the logger (`LOG`) in `POIDocument.java`.                                             
                                - The original class already declares these four members at lines 5665. The follow-up patch simply duplicated them, triggering variable is already defined                    
                             errors.                                                                                                                                                                             
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Patch Plan                                                                                                                                                                       
                                a. Open `poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/POIDocument.java`.                                                                                                                     
                                b. Remove the duplicated declarations introduced by the patch:                                                                                                                   
                                   - The extra `private SummaryInformation sInf;`                                                                                                                                
                                   - The extra `private DocumentSummaryInformation dsInf;`                                                                                                                       
                                   - The extra `private DirectoryNode directory;`                                                                                                                                
                                   - The second `private static final Logger LOG = PoiLogManager.getLogger(POIDocument.class);`                                                                                  
                                c. Leave the original definitions intact:                                                                                                                                        
                                   ```java                                                                                                                                                                       
                                   private SummaryInformation sInf;                                                                                                                                              
                                   private DocumentSummaryInformation dsInf;                                                                                                                                     
                                   private DirectoryNode directory;                                                                                                                                              
                                   private static final Logger LOG = PoiLogManager.getLogger(POIDocument.class);                                                                                                 
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                d. If additional instrumentation or logging logic is required by the fuzzer harness, reference these existing fields rather than introducing new ones.                           
                                e. Verify no other merge artifacts or duplicate blocks exist in the class.                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Preservation of Functionality                                                                                                                                                    
                                - The existing `readProperties()` and any methods using `sInf`, `dsInf`, `directory`, or `LOG` will remain unchanged and continue to function.                                   
                                - No harness code or external dependencies are modified, maintaining compatibility with the existing fuzzer setup and tests.                                                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Validation Steps                                                                                                                                                                 
                                - Rebuild the project (`:poi:compileJava`) and confirm that the duplicate-variable errors are gone.                                                                              
                                - Run the original Jazzer harness to ensure instrumentation and fuzzing behave as before with no regressions.                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Risk & Mitigation                                                                                                                                                                
                                - Side effects are minimal, as this only removes unintentionally duplicated code.                                                                                                
                                - Mitigation: a quick compile and unit-test pass will confirm no unintended deletions beyond the duplicates.                                                                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             By simply reverting the erroneous additions and using the classs preexisting fields, we eliminate the compilation errors while preserving all original logic and                   
                             ensuring the fuzzer harness continues to operate correctly.                                                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>

                             - Patch attempt                                                                                                                                                                     
                               A patch was applied to `POIDocument.java` aiming to remove duplicate metadata fields (`initialized`) and the class logger declaration. In the diff, 7 lines (a                    
                             field, its comment, and the constructor Javadoc start) were deleted and replaced by a single inline comment.

                               The build failed during `poi:compileJava` with two compiler errors at line 67 of `POIDocument.java`:                                                                              
                                  illegal start of type                                                                                                                                                       
                                  ; expected                                                                                                                                                                
                               The errors point at a stray closing Javadoc delimiter `*/`, indicating that the patch removed the matching opening comment but left its end marker intact.                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Initial issue observations                                                                                                                                                          
                              The fuzzer harness logs show standard libFuzzer and Jazzer initialization: loading hooks, instrumenting dozens of POI classes, and starting coverage-guided                       
                             fuzzing.                                                                                                                                                                            
                              No errors are present in the harness logs prior to applying any patch.                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Patch attempt details                                                                                                                                                               
                              Target file: `poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/POIDocument.java`                                                                                                                  
                              Context around line 6374 before patch:                                                                                                                                           
                                  /** For our own logging use */                                                                                                                                                 
                                  private static final Logger LOG = PoiLogManager.getLogger(POIDocument.class);                                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                  /* Have the property streams been read yet? (Only done on-demand) */                                                                                                           
                                  private boolean initialized;                                                                                                                                                   
                                  /**                                                                                                                                                                            
                                   * Constructs a POIDocument with the given directory node.                                                                                                                     
                                   *                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   * @param dir The {@link DirectoryNode} where information is read from.                                                                                                        
                                   */                                                                                                                                                                            
                                  protected POIDocument(DirectoryNode dir) {                                                                                                                                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                              Patch diff:                                                                                                                                                                       
                               - Removed the `initialized` field and its comment.                                                                                                                                
                               - Removed the Javadoc opening lines (`/**` and subsequent constructor docs) but did **not** remove the closing `*/`.                                                              
                               - Left behind an inline comment placeholder.                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Result after patch                                                                                                                                                                  
                              During `./gradlew poi:compileJava`, Java compiler errors occur:                                                                                                                   
                                  /src/poi/.../POIDocument.java:67: error: illegal start of type                                                                                                                 
                                       */                                                                                                                                                                        
                                       ^                                                                                                                                                                         
                                  /src/poi/.../POIDocument.java:67: error: ';' expected                                                                                                                          
                                       */                                                                                                                                                                        
                                        ^                                                                                                                                                                        
                              The stray `*/` is unrecognized by the compiler as it no longer corresponds to a valid comment block.                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Areas for further investigation                                                                                                                                                     
                             1. **Javadoc boundaries in POIDocument.java**                                                                                                                                       
                                - Verify that any removal of Javadoc blocks includes both the `/**` opener and `*/` closer.                                                                                      
                                - Audit surrounding lines to ensure no other partial comment delimiters remain.                                                                                                  
                             2. **Logger declaration removal**                                                                                                                                                   
                                - Confirm that removing `private static final Logger LOG` does not break other code relying on `LOG`.                                                                            
                             3. **Duplicate metadata fields**                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Examine the class to identify all occurrences of the `initialized` field or similar metadata to understand why it was considered duplicate.                                    
                             4. **Build scripts and coding conventions**                                                                                                                                         
                                - Ensure patches adhere to Apache POIs style guidelines for comments and member ordering.                                                                                       
                             5. **Compilation logs in other modules**                                                                                                                                            
                                - While the immediate failure is in `poi:compileJava`, check if related classes or generated sources reference the removed fields or logging code.

                             53: *  Document classes.                                                                                                                                                            
                             54: * Currently, this relates to Document Information Properties                                                                                                                    
                             55: */                                                                                                                                                                              
                             56:public abstract class POIDocument implements Closeable {                                                                                                                         
                             57:    /** Holds metadata on our document */                                                                                                                                        
                             58:    private SummaryInformation sInf;                                                                                                                                             
                             59:    /** Holds further metadata on our document */                                                                                                                                
                             60:    private DocumentSummaryInformation dsInf;                                                                                                                                    
                             61:    /** The directory that our document lives in */                                                                                                                              
                             62:    private DirectoryNode directory;                                                                                                                                             
                             63:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             64:    /** For our own logging use */                                                                                                                                               
                             65:    private static final Logger LOG = PoiLogManager.getLogger(POIDocument.class);                                                                                                
                             66:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             67:    /* Have the property streams been read yet? (Only done on-demand) */                                                                                                         
                             68:    private boolean initialized;                                                                                                                                                 
                             69:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             70:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             71:     * Constructs a POIDocument with the given directory node.                                                                                                                   
                             72:     *                                                                                                                                                                           
                             73:     * @param dir The {@link DirectoryNode} where information is read from.                                                                                                      
                             74:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             75:    protected POIDocument(DirectoryNode dir) {                                                                                                                                   
                             76:        this.directory = dir;                                                                                                                                                    
                             77:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             78:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             79:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             80:     * Constructs from the default POIFS                                                                                                                                         
                             81:     *                                                                                                                                                                           
                             82:     * @param fs the filesystem the document is read from                                                                                                                        
                             83:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             84:    protected POIDocument(POIFSFileSystem fs) {                                                                                                                                  
                             85:        this(fs.getRoot());                                                                                                                                                      
                             86:     }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             87:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             88:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             89:     * Fetch the Document Summary Information of the document                                                                                                                    
                             90:     *                                                                                                                                                                           
                             91:     * @return The Document Summary Information or null                                                                                                                          
                             92:     *      if it could not be read for this document.                                                                                                                           
                             93:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             94:    public DocumentSummaryInformation getDocumentSummaryInformation() {                                                                                                          
                             95:        if(!initialized) {                                                                                                                                                       
                             96:            readProperties();                                                                                                                                                    
                             97:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             98:        return dsInf;                                                                                                                                                            
                             99:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             100:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             101:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             102:     * Fetch the Summary Information of the document                                                                                                                            
                             103:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             104:     * @return The Summary information for the document or null                                                                                                                 
                             105:     *      if it could not be read for this document.                                                                                                                          
                             106:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             107:    public SummaryInformation getSummaryInformation() {                                                                                                                         
                             108:        if(!initialized) {                                                                                                                                                      
                             109:            readProperties();                                                                                                                                                   
                             110:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             111:        return sInf;                                                                                                                                                            
                             112:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             113:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             114:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             115:     * Will create whichever of SummaryInformation                                                                                                                              
                             116:     *  and DocumentSummaryInformation (HPSF) properties                                                                                                                        
                             117:     *  are not already part of your document.                                                                                                                                  
                             118:     * This is normally useful when creating a new                                                                                                                              
                             119:     *  document from scratch.                                                                                                                                                  
                             120:     * If the information properties are already there,                                                                                                                         
                             ```

                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/POIDocument.java:120-200                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             120:     * If the information properties are already there,                                                                                                                         
                             121:     *  then nothing will happen.                                                                                                                                               
                             122:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             123:    public void createInformationProperties() {                                                                                                                                 
                             124:        if (!initialized) {                                                                                                                                                     
                             125:            readProperties(false);                                                                                                                                              
                             126:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             127:        if (sInf == null) {                                                                                                                                                     
                             128:            sInf = PropertySetFactory.newSummaryInformation();                                                                                                                  
                             129:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             130:        if (dsInf == null) {                                                                                                                                                    
                             131:            dsInf = newDocumentSummaryInformation();                                                                                                                            
                             132:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             133:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             134:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             135:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             136:     * Find, and create objects for, the standard                                                                                                                               
                             137:     *  Document Information Properties (HPSF).                                                                                                                                 
                             138:     * If a given property set is missing or corrupt,                                                                                                                           
                             139:     *  it will remain null;                                                                                                                                                    
                             140:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             141:    @Internal                                                                                                                                                                   
                             142:    public void readProperties() {                                                                                                                                              
                             143:        readProperties(true);                                                                                                                                                   
                             144:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             145:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             146:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             147:     * Find, and create objects for, the standard Document Information Properties (HPSF).                                                                                       
                             148:     * If a given property set is missing or corrupt, it will remain null.                                                                                                      
                             149:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             150:     * @param warnIfNull log a warning if any of the property sets come back as null.                                                                                           
                             151:     *                   The directory is null when creating a new document from scratch                                                                                        
                             152:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             153:    @Internal                                                                                                                                                                   
                             154:    public void readProperties(boolean warnIfNull) {                                                                                                                            
                             155:        if (initialized) {                                                                                                                                                      
                             156:            return;                                                                                                                                                             
                             157:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             158:        DocumentSummaryInformation dsi = readPropertySet(DocumentSummaryInformation.class, DocumentSummaryInformation.DEFAULT_STREAM_NAME, warnIfNull);                         
                             159:        if (dsi != null) {                                                                                                                                                      
                             160:            dsInf = dsi;                                                                                                                                                        
                             161:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             162:        SummaryInformation si = readPropertySet(SummaryInformation.class, SummaryInformation.DEFAULT_STREAM_NAME, warnIfNull);                                                  
                             163:        if (si != null) {                                                                                                                                                       
                             164:            sInf = si;                                                                                                                                                          
                             165:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             166:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             167:        // Mark the fact that we've now loaded up the properties                                                                                                                
                             168:        initialized = true;                                                                                                                                                     
                             169:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             170:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             171:    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")                                                                                                                                              
                             172:    private <T> T readPropertySet(Class<T> clazz, String name, boolean warnIfNull) {                                                                                            
                             173:        String localName = clazz.getName().substring(clazz.getName().lastIndexOf('.')+1);                                                                                       
                             174:        try {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             175:            PropertySet ps = getPropertySet(name);                                                                                                                              
                             176:            if (clazz.isInstance(ps)) {                                                                                                                                         
                             177:                return (T)ps;                                                                                                                                                   
                             178:            } else if (ps != null) {                                                                                                                                            
                             179:                LOG.atWarn().log("{} property set came back with wrong class - {}", localName, ps.getClass().getName());                                                        
                             180:            } else {                                                                                                                                                            
                             181:                if (warnIfNull) {                                                                                                                                               
                             182:                    LOG.atWarn().log("{} property set came back as null", localName);                                                                                           
                             183:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             184:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             185:        } catch (IOException e) {                                                                                                                                               
                             186:            LOG.atError().withThrowable(e).log("can't retrieve property set");                                                                                                  
                             187:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             188:        return null;                                                                                                                                                            
                             189:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             190:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             191:    /**

                             208:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             209:     *  @param setName The property to read                                                                                                                                     
                             210:     *  @param encryptionInfo the encryption descriptor in case of cryptoAPI encryption                                                                                         
                             211:     *  @return The value of the given property or null if it wasn't found.

                             213:     * @throws IOException If retrieving properties fails

                             215:    @SuppressWarnings("WeakerAccess")                                                                                                                                           
                             216:    protected PropertySet getPropertySet(String setName, EncryptionInfo encryptionInfo) throws IOException {

                             218:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             219:        POIFSFileSystem encPoifs = null;                                                                                                                                        
                             220:        String step = "getting";                                                                                                                                                
                             221:        try {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             222:            if (encryptionInfo != null && encryptionInfo.isDocPropsEncrypted()) {                                                                                               
                             223:                step = "getting encrypted";                                                                                                                                     
                             224:                String encryptedStream = getEncryptedPropertyStreamName();                                                                                                      
                             225:                if (!dirNode.hasEntryCaseInsensitive(encryptedStream)) {                                                                                                        
                             226:                    throw new EncryptedDocumentException("can't find encrypted property stream '"+encryptedStream+"'");                                                         
                             227:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             228:                CryptoAPIDecryptor dec = (CryptoAPIDecryptor)encryptionInfo.getDecryptor();                                                                                     
                             229:                encPoifs = dec.getSummaryEntries(dirNode, encryptedStream);                                                                                                     
                             230:                dirNode = encPoifs.getRoot();

                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. **Revert faulty removals around line 6375**                                                                                                                                     
                                - The previous patch incorrectly deleted critical code and its Javadoc opener while leaving behind a stray `*/`, triggering the illegal start of type and ;                 
                             expected errors. We must undo that.                                                                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. **Remove the stray closing Javadoc delimiter**                                                                                                                                   
                                - Delete the unpaired line containing only `*/`.                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. **Restore the `initialized` field and its comment**                                                                                                                              
                                - Reinsert:                                                                                                                                                                      
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                  /* Have the property streams been read yet? (Only done on-demand) */                                                                                                           
                                  private boolean initialized;                                                                                                                                                   
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - This flag is essential for the lazy-loading guards in `getSummaryInformation()`, `getDocumentSummaryInformation()`, `createInformationProperties()`, and                       
                             `readProperties(...)`.                                                                                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. **Restore the constructor Javadoc**                                                                                                                                              
                                - Re-add immediately above the `protected POIDocument(DirectoryNode dir)` constructor:                                                                                           
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                  /**                                                                                                                                                                            
                                   * Constructs a POIDocument with the given directory node.                                                                                                                     
                                   *                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   * @param dir The {@link DirectoryNode} where information is read from.                                                                                                        
                                   */                                                                                                                                                                            
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - This ensures the Javadoc is balanced and satisfies coding conventions.                                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. **Preserve the logger declaration**                                                                                                                                              
                                - Do not remove:                                                                                                                                                                 
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                  /** For our own logging use */                                                                                                                                                 
                                  private static final Logger LOG = PoiLogManager.getLogger(POIDocument.class);                                                                                                  
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - Logging calls (`LOG.atWarn()`, `LOG.atError()`, etc.) in `readPropertySet(...)` and elsewhere depend on this field.                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. **Delete the placeholder comment**                                                                                                                                               
                                - Remove the line:                                                                                                                                                               
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                  // Removed duplicate metadata fields and logger declaration                                                                                                                    
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - It no longer reflects the code and blocks proper Javadoc alignment.                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             7. **Validate coding style and recompile**                                                                                                                                          
                                - Align indentation and spacing to Apache POI conventions.                                                                                                                       
                                - Run `./gradlew poi:compileJava` to ensure no remaining compile errors.                                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             8. **Rationale and sideeffect mitigation**                                                                                                                                         
                                - *Why this works*: Removing the lone `*/` and restoring the Javadoc opener balances the comment block, resolving the compile errors. Restoring `initialized`                    
                             and `LOG` preserves existing lazy-loading and logging logic, preventing unintended behavioral regressions.                                                                          
                                - *Potential side effects*: None expected, since we revert to the original, tested code paths. Existing behavior around property reading and logging remains                     
                             identical.                                                                                                                                                                          
                                - *No external or harness code changes*: We only modify `POIDocument.java`. All tests and fuzzer harnesses continue to operate unchanged.                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>
